{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/to-beard-or-not-to-beard-that-is-the-question-b46864d7e003", "time": 1683011357.629777, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/to-beard-or-not-to-beard-that-is-the-question-b46864d7e003/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "To Beard, or not to Beard, That is the Question | by Cody Glickman, PhD | Towards Data Science", "h1": "To Beard, or not to Beard, That is the Question", "description": "Machine learning applied to computer vision is a growing field in data science and some interesting problems have been solved using these methods. Computer vision is identifying poachers and bringing\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://phys.org/news/2018-02-ai-vision-breakthrough-ids-poachers.html", "anchor_text": "identifying poachers", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://opencv.org/", "anchor_text": "OpenCV", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://www.pyimagesearch.com/2020/04/13/opencv-age-detection-with-deep-learning/", "anchor_text": "Adrian Rosebrock\u2019s pyimagesearch tutorial", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/age-detection-using-facial-images-traditional-machine-learning-vs-deep-learning-2437b2feeab2", "anchor_text": "Prerak Agarwal\u2019s TDS post", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://github.com/Datadolittle/2BeardorNot2Beard", "anchor_text": "GitHub", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1gN7GoxYRAfE_wuiQaaR6dJ7qWD1kZ0Dz", "anchor_text": "Prerak\u2019s CoLab", "paragraph_index": 1}, {"url": "https://www.kaggle.com/frabbisw/facial-age", "anchor_text": "facial-age dataset", "paragraph_index": 1}, {"url": "https://susanqq.github.io/UTKFace/", "anchor_text": "UTKFace dataset", "paragraph_index": 1}, {"url": "https://docs.opencv.org/3.4/db/d28/tutorial_cascade_classifier.html", "anchor_text": "Cascade Classifiers", "paragraph_index": 2}, {"url": "https://github.com/Datadolittle/2BeardorNot2Beard", "anchor_text": "Github", "paragraph_index": 3}, {"url": "https://codyglickman.com/", "anchor_text": "Cody Glickman", "paragraph_index": 7}, {"url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/codyglickman/", "anchor_text": "LinkedIn", "paragraph_index": 7}, {"url": "https://codyglickman.com/", "anchor_text": "https://codyglickman.com/", "paragraph_index": 9}], "all_paragraphs": ["Machine learning applied to computer vision is a growing field in data science and some interesting problems have been solved using these methods. Computer vision is identifying poachers and bringing them to justice as well as powering the wave of self-driving cars. In this article, I am using computer vision for a more irrelevant reason, age identification of myself with and without a beard. I incorporate a lot of my code and reasoning from prior posts that you should definitely check out if you are interested in age prediction using machine learning. OpenCV is a must if your interested in computer vision and there are many tutorials to help you get started. The code for this article was adapted from Adrian Rosebrock\u2019s pyimagesearch tutorial. I also went through the exercise of training my own models using Prerak Agarwal\u2019s TDS post. My adapted code is available on GitHub, although I recommend checking out the code from both Adrian and Prerak. My scripts utilizes pre-built CAFFE models due to long training times in Tensorflow.", "To train any model for a classification task such as age prediction, we require labeled face data with true ages. To train your own deep learning models using Tensorflow, Prerak\u2019s CoLab notebooks are a great place to start. He begins by creating age ranges or bins of evenly distributed labeled training data. In my own model training, I changed the bins to more accurately represent developmental stages. For example, I split the large category of 10\u201320 into 8\u201312, 13\u201316, and 17\u201325. However, in a combination of the facial-age dataset and the UTKFace dataset an enrichment of 17\u201325 and 25\u201330 year olds was present. After training, I tested my new deep learning model on the left out testing dataset and discovered my model predicted all test cases as 25\u201330. This was probably a result of the unbalanced training data. I would need to down sample my training data to balance my classes to deal with this issue. Instead of continuing to fiddle with my own modeling, I turned to the pre-trained models in Adrian\u2019s tutorial.", "To implement the age classification model, one must first find all faces in a picture. OpenCV has facial classifier demos using Cascade Classifiers. Thankfully, the facial detection model was already created. We can just find faces then create a rectangular box to highlight the \u201cblob\u201d our model identified to predict age and gender. Blob is a term for subsection of an image. Our script runs new blob predictions forward through the network and takes the maximum prediction score. The maximum prediction score is the term assigned to the face predicted.", "To run the script simply download the source code and models from the project Github. Opencv will need to be installed to run the models and the scripts using", "Then head into the folder and play around with some photos. **The photo to classify must be in the same directory as the AgeGender.py to print the output file.**", "This will output the file age-gender-out-bearded_willy.jpg. Open that file to see the classification performance.", "How does this age classification system work against my own beard/no beard pictures.", "This age classification system rates my no beard face as between 15\u201320. Given I am almost 30 now, I think keeping the beard around will allow future facial recognition technology to accurately identify my age range. My name is Cody Glickman and I can be found on LinkedIn. Be sure to check out some other articles below.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "Currently a biological data scientist blogging about side projects and things learned through brute force. https://codyglickman.com/"], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2Fb46864d7e003&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fto-beard-or-not-to-beard-that-is-the-question-b46864d7e003&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fto-beard-or-not-to-beard-that-is-the-question-b46864d7e003&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fnew-story&source=---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------new_post_sidenav-----------", "anchor_text": "Write"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/search?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fto-beard-or-not-to-beard-that-is-the-question-b46864d7e003&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fto-beard-or-not-to-beard-that-is-the-question-b46864d7e003&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/?source=post_page-----b46864d7e003--